[[[description]]]
This object flag is used to denote that guards are being used for an object. This occurs when any property accessor magic methods (`__set`, `__isset`, `__unset`, `__get`) have been implemented on the corresponding class entry (see also the [`ZEND_ACC_USE_GUARDS`](https://phpinternals.net/docs/zend_acc_use_guards) class entry flag), and as such, they should be used for property access.

